Package: seedhash
Type: Package
Title: Deterministic Seed Generation from String Inputs Using MD5 Hashing
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("melhzy", email = "melhzy@gmail.com", 
                  role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides a simple way to generate reproducible random seeds from 
    string inputs using MD5 hashing. Useful for reproducible experiments and 
    simulations where deterministic random number generation based on a string 
    identifier is needed. The package uses R6 classes to create seed generators 
    that convert text strings into numeric seeds via MD5 hashing.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
Imports:
    digest,
    R6
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
URL: https://github.com/melhzy/seedhash
BugReports: https://github.com/melhzy/seedhash/issues
